not values) requires const generics or associated types, which may be too complex for 150 connectors. The value-level ZoneBound wrapper with runtime check is a pragmatic middle ground that still enforces the binding at the API level. WHERE: crates/fcp-core/src/zone.rs or new module. Used in fcp-host when creating connector instances. ACCEPTANCE: (1) ZoneBound<T> type exists. (2) Connector instances wrapped in ZoneBound. (3) Operations require zone match check. (4) Cross-zone operation returns ZoneViolation error. (5) At least 4 tests: bind and access within zone, cross-zone access rejected, zone_id accessor, serialization. ESTIMATED EFFORT: 2-3 days. DEPENDS ON: C3.1 (phantom tokens) — the zone binding interacts with token zone_id validation.","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:36:52Z"},{"id":2660,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-qmy9x","author":"jemanuel","text":"C3.7 complete: (1) ZoneBound<T> type exists with bind(), zone_id(), with_zone_check(), with_zone_check_mut(), into_inner(). (2) Cross-zone access returns FcpError::ZoneViolation. (3) Serde roundtrip works. (4) Zone immutable after binding. (5) 8 acceptance tests. Commit ac6996dd.","created_at":"2026-04-10T23:20:34Z"}]}
