+{"id":"flywheel_connectors-uxsnk","title":"[CRITICAL] Peer-signed RevocationPushMessage bypasses Owner-signature authority","description":"crates/fcp-mesh/src/gossip.rs:945 + RevocationPushMessage is signed only by a peer node (from) but carries a list of revoked_ids. Recipient MeshNode::handle_revocation_push verifies the peer signature but does not verify that the revoked IDs were actually signed by the zone owner. A compromised peer can broadcast pushes that revoke any object or node in the mesh without owner authority.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T20:39:37.768753Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-21T21:33:40.904836Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T21:33:40.903618Z","close_reason":"c14bf948 enforces zone-owner signature on RevocationPushMessage at fcp-mesh node.rs handle_revocation_push","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":2819,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-uxsnk","author":"jemanuel","text":"Landed in c14bf948. Two-layer signing contract: peer signature (transport) + owner_signature (NORMATIVE authorization). Added RevocationPushMessage::owner_signing_bytes() (FCP2-REVOCATION-OWNER-V1 || zone || sorted revoked_ids || new_rev_seq — excludes peer+timestamp so a single owner sig survives forwarding) and verify_owner_signature(). MeshNode gains zone_owner_keys map + register_zone_owner_key(). handle_revocation_push now fails closed with UnknownZoneOwner/MissingOwnerSignature/InvalidOwnerSignature before accepting any revocation. 6/6 revocation push tests pass (happy path + missing owner sig + forged owner sig + unregistered zone owner + stale-after-sigs + unknown peer). MultiNodeMeshHarness retrofitted with a shared zone_owner_signing_key and a RegisterZoneOwnerKey NodeCommand so the verified-dispatch-boundary integration test continues to exercise the positive path. Pre-existing coordinator::tests::acquire_* failures are unrelated (confirmed by re-running on git stash)."